The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Brown weeps
                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Brown weeps
                            
	London, Feb. 7: Gordon Brown wept when he talked of the death of his daughter Jennifer during a TV interview, it has emerged.         
	The British Prime Ministers eyes filled with tears as he told Piers Morgan he knew that his newborn daughter was not going to survive.         
	She died in 2002 aged just 10 days after suffering a brain haemorrhage.         
	The exchange took place in front of a live studio audience and is due to be broadcast on ITV next Sunday.         
	Brown also spoke of his three-year-old son Frasers battle with cystic fibrosis.         
	Other topics reportedly covered during the interview include an admission that he occasionally lost his temper, confirmation of explosive rows with former Prime Minister Tony Blair, and the fact that Blair had secretly promised to hand over power to him  but that the timing lay with his predecessor.                     THE SUNDAY TELEGRAPH                                                                                                                                                  
